The National Working Committee (NWC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) on Wednesday extended the sale of expression of interest and nomination gorms for the 2023 general elections to Tuesday, May 10, 2022. The extension was contained in a statement by the National Publicity Secretary, Barr. Felix Morka in Abuja The party had fixed the closing date for the sale of nomination forms for Friday, May 6 2022.   Emir of Kano urges residents to collect PVCs     Nigeria-Morocco gas pipeline: OPEC, Russia show interest     Agents to drag Customs, Ministry to National Assembly over…   According to the statement, a revised timetable by the party’s National Organising Secretary, H.E. Sulaiman Muhammad Argungu showed that submission of completed forms and accompanying documents is now set for Wednesday May 11, 2022. The party also fixed congresses to elect Local Government Area, State and National delegates to hold from Thursday, 12th May to Saturday, 14th May, 2022. The congresses were fixed for May 7- 9, May 2022.